  "prompt": "What is the minimum marks needed to get mechanical branch in BITS Pilani?",
  "response": "The minimum marks required to secure admission into the Mechanical Engineering program at BITS Pilani can vary each year based on several factors, including the overall performance of applicants, the number of seats available, and the cut-off trends for that particular admission cycle. Historically, admission to BITS Pilani is based on the BITS Admission Test (BITSAT) scores.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding cut-offs, it's best to check the official BITS Pilani admission website or consult recent admission statistics. Generally, competitive scores are required, so prospective students should aim for a high BITSAT score to increase their chances of admission into popular branches like Mechanical Engineering.",
